# Astro Agent — Cursor Rules (Auto-loaded Context)

## Project
Production-ready Astrologer AI Agent with RAG. Vedic astrology + palmistry PDFs → OCR → embeddings → vector search → LLM answer.

## Stack
- OCR: Tesseract + pytesseract + pdf2image
- Diagram interpretation: GPT-4o (one-time ingestion only)
- Embeddings: OpenAI text-embedding-3-small
- Vector DB: ChromaDB (local dev), Pinecone (production)
- Inference: GPT-4o-mini
- Backend: FastAPI
- Frontend: Streamlit (dev) → React (prod)
- Auth: Supabase + Stripe

## Folder Structure
ingestion/          → pdf_processor.py, image_extractor.py, translator.py, chunker.py, embedder.py
retrieval/          → query_engine.py, image_retriever.py
agent/              → astrologer.py, prompt_builder.py, session_manager.py, chart_calculator.py
api/                → main.py, routes/, auth.py
frontend/           → app.py
data/pdfs/          → source PDFs (English + Hindi)
data/chroma_db/     → persistent vector store
data/extracted_images/ → diagram images
data/default_user/  → kundali_summary.txt, palm_description.txt
data/sessions/      → per-session JSON files

## File Dependency Map
pdf_processor → chunker → translator → embedder → ChromaDB
query_engine + chart_calculator → astrologer → session_manager

## translator.py
- NO IndicTrans2 — rejected; produces broken English on classical Sanskrit texts. Use GPT-4o-mini for Hindi prose.
- Sanskrit/diagrams: GPT-4o vision via image_extractor.py

## Chunk Metadata Schema (locked — do not change)
{
  "chunk_id": "str",          # "{book_name}_p{page_num}_c{index}"
  "text": "str",
  "topic": "str",
  "language": "eng|hin|mixed",
  "page_ref": "int",
  "image_path": "str|null",
  "book_name": "str",
  "page_type": "text|diagram|mixed",
  "word_count": "int"
}

## ChromaDB
- Collection name: "astro_chunks"
- Embedding dimension: 1536 (text-embedding-3-small)
- Persist directory: data/chroma_db/

## Coding Standards
- Python 3.11; always try/except with meaningful errors; surgical edits only
- Preserve all interfaces and metadata schemas
- User is senior analytics practitioner — no basics

## AI Review Standards

### Code Review Discipline
- NEVER rubber-stamp Claude Code or AI output — review every diff critically
- Always check: does this match original design intent? Are interfaces preserved?
- Flag logic errors, missing guards, threshold issues BEFORE accepting edits

### Testing Strategy
- Test the HARDEST case first — not the easiest
- Sample before full runs: 20 pages before 500, 1 book before 5 books
- If a full run takes >10 min, find a faster validation path first

### Auto-suggestion Discipline
- Auto-suggestions are NOT instructions — evaluate before accepting
- "Proceed" and "looks good" require explicit reasoning, not pattern matching

### Threshold and Logic Review
- Every threshold needs a scope guard (e.g. word_count) to prevent noise triggering
- Check logic ORDER — conditions evaluate top to bottom; order matters
- Low thresholds (< 0.20, < 2) need explicit justification; start conservative, tune down

### Debugging
- Isolate and validate components before running full pipeline
- Human checkpoint between AI-generated code and production runs

## Multi-Agent Review Process

Before writing ANY new file or component:
1. Load .claude/architect.md — review structure
2. Load .claude/business.md — review user value
3. Load .claude/critic.md — challenge assumptions
4. Load .claude/qa.md — validate test coverage
5. Reconcile all four before writing code

Mandatory for: new files, schema changes, threshold values, pipeline changes, API integrations
